# Bash Component Patterns

- Keep scripts Bash-first and consistent with nearby files; avoid introducing heavier tooling for simple install steps.
- Name **all Bash functions in camelCase** (no `snake_case` or leading underscores); match helpers in [`src/`](/src/) (e.g. `registerBuildMetadata`, `showUsage`, `ensureShellRcRegion`, `ensureWslConfIniLine`, `getFile`, `printInfo`).

## Metadata and dispatch (`conf.sh`, `install.sh`)

- `conf.sh` calls `registerBuildMetadata` ([`src/builder/build-metadata.sh`](../../src/builder/build-metadata.sh)): `BUILD_DIR_NAME` (usually basename of `builds/<name>/`), `BUILD_VER`, CSV of valid components, `NUM_ADDITIONAL_ARGS`.
- **ai-resources:** optional `AI_RESOURCES_PROJECT_DIR` in user `wsl-builds.conf`; `conf.sh` sets `PROJECT_DIR` (default `$HOME/ai-resources`) for per-component `builds/<name>/<slug>/install.sh` scripts.
- Add new components to the **third argument** CSV. Hyphens in tokens map to underscores in the per-component directory name (`mysql-client` → `builds/<name>/mysql_client/install.sh`).
- `install.sh` is only `source "${TOOL_DIR}/src/builder/install-dispatch.sh"`. **`./wsl-builder.sh`** sets `TOOL_DIR` to the repository root (the same absolute path as `REPO_ROOT`) before sourcing this file. The dispatch loop runs **at top level** in `src/builder/install-dispatch.sh` (no wrapper) so **the builder** stays the entrypoint and `$@` propagates when `install.sh` is sourced. **Do not** add per-component `if`/`source` in `install.sh` or duplicate dispatch logic.
- After each per-component `install.sh` finishes, **`src/builder/install-dispatch.sh`** calls `recordComponentSuccess` with the **canonical component token (hyphens preserved)** so `~/.wsl-build.info` lines stay stable and `BUILD_UPDATED=true`; partial success is still recorded if a later component fails. **Do not** call `recordComponentSuccess` inside `builds/<name>/<slug>/install.sh`.
- **`isComponentInstalled`:** checks `~/.wsl-build.info`; respects `--force`. Returns 0 if already installed, 1 if not (or when `--force` skips the short-circuit).
- **`warnComponentAlreadyInstalled`:** use for the standard “already installed” warning (includes `--force` hint).

## Shell and WSL config

- `~/.bashrc` / `~/.zshrc`: use `ensureShellRcRegion`, `replaceManagedShellRcRegion`, or `removeManagedShellRcRegion` from [`src/builder/shell-rc.sh`](../../src/builder/shell-rc.sh) (named `wsl-builds:<id>` blocks), not ad hoc `grep` + `>>`.
- `/etc/wsl.conf`: use `ensureWslConfIniLine` from [`src/builder/wsl-conf.sh`](../../src/builder/wsl-conf.sh) for idempotent section lines (with `sudo`).
- Put component logic in `builds/<name>/<slug>/install.sh` (`slug` = token with hyphens mapped to underscores).

## apt (Ubuntu)

- Run `sudo apt update` before repo-backed `sudo apt install`; always pass `-y`; use `apt` not `apt-get`. Skip `apt update` for local `.deb` / `dpkg -i` only. Flow: `printInfo "Installing X"` → `sudo apt update` → `sudo apt install -y …` → optional `printInfo "X version: …"` → `printInfo "X installed"`.

## Downloads, caches, `set -e`

- **`getFile`:** caches under `CACHE_DIR`; uses a `/tmp` working area—failed runs do not require manual cleanup across reboot. Pair with **`cleanupGetFiles`** after installers when you want explicit cleanup.
- **Large / durable caches:** optional `wsl-builds.conf` vars (**UPPER_SNAKE_CASE**, tool-scoped), sourced by **the builder** before installs; gate with `[ -n "${VAR:-}" ]`; add commented examples to `wsl-builds.conf.example` and document in the build `README.md`. See `builds/ai-resources/sg3/install.sh`, `builds/ai/ollama/install.sh`.
- **`./wsl-builder.sh`** uses `set -euo pipefail`—avoid broad error swallowing; you generally cannot rely on in-script cleanup after a failed command. Generic libraries under `src/` do not enable strict mode; new entrypoints should follow [`docs/standardise-bootstrap-plan.md`](../../docs/standardise-bootstrap-plan.md) and [`src/common/bootstrap-common.sh`](../../src/common/bootstrap-common.sh).

## Component messaging

- **Open:** `printInfo "Installing <Name>"` (same noun at close).
- **In progress:** `printInfo` steps, no ellipsis (`…` / `...`).
- **Close:** `printInfo "<Name> installed"` — past tense, no “successfully”, no ellipsis, no trailing period; **last** user-facing status after any verification.
- **Channels:** `printInfo` / `printWarning` / `printError` for status; `echo` only for heredocs / file payloads.
- **Optional version:** `printInfo "<Name> version: $(cmd …)"` (or first line). No `2>/dev/null || echo …` fallbacks.
- **Golden example:** [`builds/dev-js/node/install.sh`](../../builds/dev-js/node/install.sh).
- **Tests:** changing fixed `print*` / prompts / usage text can break `test/docker/*.bats`. `rg` `test/` and `builds/test-fixture/` for old substrings and update in the **same change**; run `./test/run-tests.sh` after substantive `src/` or `./wsl-builder.sh` messaging edits.

## Optional: disable start on boot (systemd)

Vendor installs may `systemctl enable` a unit. After substantive install (before final `printInfo "<Name> installed"`), you may offer an opt-out: gate on `command -v systemctl` and the unit, **`promptYesNo`**, then `sudo systemctl disable --now <unit>`. Components with multiple systemd units (e.g. Docker) keep `disable --now` order **in the component**—no generic `src/` helper until several callers match. EOF/non-interactive skips disable (CI-safe). **Do not** add without the user agreeing in that task. Examples: [`builds/ai/ollama/install.sh`](../../builds/ai/ollama/install.sh), [`builds/devops/docker/install.sh`](../../builds/devops/docker/install.sh), [`builds/db/mysql_server/install.sh`](../../builds/db/mysql_server/install.sh), [`builds/db/postgres_server/install.sh`](../../builds/db/postgres_server/install.sh). Document new prompts in the build `README.md`; check `test/` for assertions on new strings.

## Repo root Build List (`README.md`)

**Scope:** top-level repo `README.md` only—not `builds/<name>/README.md`.

- When user-visible builds or components change, update the **Build List** table. Keep that README for **end users** (install, `./wsl-builder.sh`, the list). **No** meta lines about how the table is written (“one row per build”, “bold means …”). Table styling conventions belong in rules, not user-facing prose. See [readme-user-facing.mdc](readme-user-facing.mdc) for tone.
- **Columns:** **Build** | **Packages, Frameworks, Tools & Extras** | **Additional Conf**.
- **Middle column:** every component (bold token, short description). Read each `builds/<name>/<slug>/install.sh` first. List **substantive installs / framework scaffolds** before **QoL, wrappers, DX-only layers, workaround fixes**. *Substantive:* OS/vendor packages (runtimes, SDKs, CUDA, DBs, `docker`, `awscli`, infra CLIs, `x11` / `smb` / `nfs` / `systemd` / `wslu`), framework installers (`react`, `nextjs`, **ai-resources** pieces), `essentials` / `update`, `node` / `nvm` / `yarn`, `python3` / `conda`, `shellcheck`, `bats`, `hugo`, `jekyll`, `ollama`. *QoL / thin / fix:* e.g. dev-js `essentials` (npm globals), `qol`, `fstab`, `vscode`, `cursor`, devops-aws `qol`, `cuda-wsl-lib-symlinks`. Mixed components (e.g. `cursor`): order by **primary purpose**, not by whether `apt` appears.
- **Additional Conf:** `wsl-builds.conf` keys this build reads (see `wsl-builds.conf.example`). Prefix each group with **`component`:** like the middle column. Separate groups with `<br/>`. Target **~30 characters per visual line**; add `<br/>` without **splitting tokens** (no breaks inside env names, `GIT_*`, or bold labels). One key shared by all components: comma-separated bold tokens before the colon (e.g. **ai-resources**: **sg3**, **lsd**, **spleeter**, **rudalle**). Empty cell if none. Omit builder-global keys (`CACHE_DIR`, `EXTERNAL_BUILDS_ROOT`, …) from rows unless there is a strong reason to repeat.

## Test fixture

- **`builds/test-fixture/`** is **testing-only**: noop per-component `install.sh` files. See [`builds/test-fixture/README.md`](../../builds/test-fixture/README.md) and [`test/README.md`](../../test/README.md).
